    "name": "HT-MC-BTC-CLM-PAM-MirrorPassthrough-AllocDrift-LiqBuffer-6m0",
    "description": "ACTUS Hybrid Treasury v4: BTC CLM + Cash PAM MIRROR PASSTHROUGH\n\n=== MIRROR PASSTHROUGH vs SIGNAL MULTIPLIER ===\nv3 (CashPAM file): uses signalMultiplier=-4.0 on ad_btc01_cash.\n  Works, but requires manual calculation of scale factor ($2M/$500K=4).\n  Rounding errors compound; BTC NP reduction doesn't perfectly match cash NP increase.\n\nv4 (THIS FILE): uses mirrorSourceModelId on ad_btc01_mirror.\n  Source model (ad_btc01) caches dollar payoff in dollarPayoffCache.\n  Mirror model reads cache, returns -(sourceDollars / mirrorNP).\n  GUARANTEED dollar-for-dollar: if source sells $148K BTC, mirror adds $148K cash.\n  No scale factor needed. No rounding errors.\n\n=== ARCHITECTURE ===\nad_btc01 (source, on CLM):\n  Normal AllocationDriftModel. Computes allocation = (qty × spotPrice) / portfolioTotal.\n  After each stateAt(): caches dollar payoff = signal × currentNP into dollarPayoffCache.\n\nad_btc01_mirror (mirror, on PAM cash):\n  mirrorSourceModelId = 'ad_btc01'\n  stateAt() reads: sourceDollars = ad_btc01.dollarPayoffCache[time]\n  Returns: -(sourceDollars / cashNP)\n  PP event on cash PAM: payoff = -(sourceDollars / cashNP) × cashNP = -sourceDollars\n  Negative PP = NP increase = cash inflow ✓\n\nCONTRACT ORDERING: CLM contract MUST appear before PAM cash contract.\n  ACTUS processes contracts sequentially. Source stateAt() must run first\n  to populate dollarPayoffCache before mirror reads it.\n\nPortfolio (6 contracts):\n  Contract 1: CLM  — 40 BTC ($2M @ $50K) lent at 3% APY → ad_btc01\n  Contract 2: PAM  — $500K fiat cash reserve (0% interest) → ad_btc01_mirror + lb_tr01\n  Contract 3-6: PAM — T-Bills ($500K Mar, $500K May, $250K Jun, $500K Jul)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
